Easiest to obtain these days is blue diamond gear, last time I saw, that stuff was sold at even lower prices than the blue diamonds themselves. Still: cool resists, and it gets the job done.<br>
Tad more expensive is the cazicite gear. Cazicite blue diamond and cazicite black sapphire, that sort of stuff. Cazicite is harder to collect, but the jewelry has the advantage that, apart from the resists, it also has some +HP attached to it: no matter what class you are, when it's time to worry about your resists, it's time to worry about your hitpoints...<br>
Perhaps the best thing you can do, is look at your gear and try, using your neck, head, ear, wrist and ring slots to get each of your resists to, or slightly over, 100. As a rule of thumb, 100 is considered &quot;sufficient&quot; against most normal raid targets. Once your resists are at 100, you can stop worrying about them for a pretty long time. Maybe <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.eqtraders.com/recipes/recipe_page.php?article=49&amp;rsa=Jewelcraft&amp;sb=item&amp;sub=enchanted&amp;menustr=080070010000" target="top">this list</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> on EQTraders can help...<br>
<br>
Now, depending on your class, another thing that you could prolly consider is this...<br>
A lot of raid mobs have AE's with a range of 200. Now, that is also the range of a lot of player's spells. Some classes, like rangers and mages have even wider ranges for their arrows and bolts, so all they have to do is stand a good end away from the mob and, as long as they control their agro, they won't have to worry about that AE at all.<br>
Now, for a bunch of other classes (wizards, druids, and I believe shamans and a couple of others) an extended range item is often a great alternative for a bunch of resist items, as long as the zone allows you that room of course. Ceramic Sword of War goes for a few k in the bazaar (/waves Dyrna) and can make the difference between having the killshot on a dragon and needing a rez. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.wxs.nl/~tom.van.der.veen/Sig-custom.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#660066><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub22.ezboard.com/brutabagaparadoxforum.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bettik@rutabagaparadoxforum>Bettik</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The One 2 Blame!!!!!1!</span><br>  Posts: 191<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(9/26/03 5:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub22.ezboard.com/frutabagaparadoxforumgeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1412.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Resist Gear</span><hr size=1> Heh.. We should have a forum called &quot;Ask Ete&quot; <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
